<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f99794380668319>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>RE: wurmslayer rocks</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Aug 16th 2:36 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=18005><span id= >Balker</span></a><br><span id=notbold>55 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.10]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well, the problem with Wurmslayer, from a warrior perspective, is it's too slow to taunt.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you have 2 warriors, both the same level, both start swinging at the same time.  One is using a lammy in in the primary the other is using a Wurmslayer, the first swing the wurmslayer will have agro.  The second swing the Lammy will take over agro because the wurmslayer will still be cycling thru, the third swing, still the lammy.  Finally when the wurmslayer cycles thru, depending where the wurmslayer weilding warrior is on the hate list, (not taking taunt into account)  he will be at the bottom list.  So, that is why a Lammy is better than a wurmslayer.  As a warrior you're not there for dealing damage, your job is to take the damage.<br><br>Taunt basically puts you on the top of the hate list for that round until someone out damages and moves up.  If you're using a faster weapon you will be holding your position as the #1 hated guy in the group, for the most part.. sometimes you get those over casting wizards who try to kill the mob in one blow =)<br><br>So, basically, that's why I've never wanted nor will I ever use a Wurmslayer.<br><br>Balker Neehigh<br>55 Warrior<br>The Commune<br>Xegony</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
