	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f99891414668854>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=2680&mid=99891414668854>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=2680&mid=99891414668854>RE: wurmslayer rocks</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=2680&mid=99891414668854#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Aug 27th 8:09 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=18005><span id= >Balker</span></a><br><span id=notbold>55 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.15]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>hmm, go for it man.&nbsp;&nbsp;Not saying you can't, just saying damage out put isn't where a Warrior excels.  If you want to be melee and deal damage, play a monk or rogue they easly out damage warriors, even the ones using Wurmslayers, but they stand a chance to take the beating you can and will/should be taking.<br><br>At level 40 your soloing days are just about over if not, they've been over for at least 5 levels now.  Once you hit 50 you better look at what's going to benifit the group or raid the most.  What most other classes want is a warrior that will take the hits.  In order for you to take the hits (and keep the mobs hitting you) is to build up hate, the slower the weapon the lower you'll be on the hate list, the lower on the hate list the more the shaman or enchanter or rogue is getting beat on.  The more they're getting beat on the more your group is going to be asking "Are you taunting???" Finally, once the chanter dies all hell will break lose and the whole group dies or evacs, assuming the druid wasn't getting beat on because they're snare put them higer on the hate list than you.<br><br>I agree with you.  I think it would be great if I could do more damage, unfortunately to be usefull to a group or raid, your crits for 180 points don't help them much, you hitting quickly to keep the mob on you is what they want.  So, because I like getting exp and I like grouping with people and I like going on raids I do what I have to so I can benifit the group.<br><br>Balker Neehigh<br>56 Warrior<br>The Commune<br>Xegony</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
